      If the specified Object, a NullPointerException with no error message (default constructor) is thrown.
      Type Parameters:

    • nullCheck

      public static <T> T nullCheck​(T obj, String name, String info)
      Checks if the specified Object is not null.
      If the specified Object is null, a NullPointerException with the specified error message is thrown.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The generic type of obj.
      Parameters:
      obj - The Object being null-checked.
      name - The name of the Object being null-checked.
      1. If name is null, the NullPointerException, if thrown, will not have an error message.
      2. If name is not null, the NullPointerException that is thrown will specify the name in its error message.
      info - Any additional information that would be useful to print in the error message.
      Specify null if no additional information is required.
      Returns:
      The specified Object (if non-null).
      See Also:
      nullCheckMessage(Object, String)

    • boundsCheck

      public static <T extends Number> T boundsCheck​(T value, double floor, double ceiling, boolean isFloorInclusive, boolean isCeilingInclusive, String valueName)
      Checks if the specified value is within the specified bounds defined by the specified floor and ceiling.
      If the specified value is not within the specified bounds, an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown.

      Example: 

       long myNumber = 1000;
 int number = check(myNumber, -50, 750, "My Number");
      The example above does the following:
      1. Creates a variable of type long equal to 1000 called myVariable.
      2. Uses the check method to check if the bounds of myVariable are between -50 and 750.
      3. Determines that myVariable is not within the specified bounds (750 is less than 1000
      4. Throws a IndexOutOfBoundsException
      This method will never return null.
      Parameters:
      value - The value being bounds-checked.
      valueName - The name of the value.
      Returns:
      The specified value (if the bounds-check is successful).
